#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:2
msgid "Creating SSH Keypairs on Windows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:4
msgid ""
"This walkthrough will show you how to create SSH keys for use with Juju on "
"the Windows OS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:8
msgid "1. Create the .ssh folder"
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:10
msgid ""
"First you need to create a folder called .ssh in your Home directory, which "
"is where ssh keys will be kept."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:13
msgid ""
"One way to do this is to open the Start Menu and type \"cmd\" (without "
"quotes) in the search box at the bottom of the Start Menu. Click on cmd.exe "
"when it comes up in the search results. This will open up a Windows command "
"prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:18
msgid "Type the following in the command prompt:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:25
msgid "This will create a folder called .ssh in your home directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:28
msgid "2. Download puttygen.exe"
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:30
msgid ""
"Download puttygen.exe from the `PuTTY download page`_ The file you download "
"is not an installer, but a simple executable you can run directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:34
msgid ""
"Once downloaded, run puttygen.exe, you should see a dialog that looks like "
"this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:39
msgid "3. Generating your keys"
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:41
msgid ""
"The defaults for the parameters at the bottom of the window are correct "
"(SSH-2 RSA and 2048 bits). Click generate, and move your mouse back and "
"forth over the window to generate your key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:45
msgid ""
"It is recommended that you specify a passphrase (password) for your key, so "
"that if it is lost, it can't be used without the password. Choose a password"
" you can remember, because it cannot be recovered if forgotten."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:51
msgid "4. Save your keys"
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:53
msgid ""
"Click Conversions->Export OpenSSH Key on the main menu. Find the .ssh folder"
" you created earlier and save the key in that folder with the name id_rsa "
"(no extension). This is where Juju and some other programs will look for it "
"by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:58
msgid ""
"Next, you need to save your public key. To do this, right click in the box "
"under \"Public key for pasting into OpenSSH authorized_keys file\", and "
"click \"Select All\". Copy the text using Ctrl-C or right-click Copy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:63
msgid ""
"Open Notepad and paste the contents of the clipboard. Save the file with the"
" name id_rsa.pub in the same directory where you saved the private key "
"(note, the extension should be .pub, not .txt)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting-started-keygen-win.rst:67
msgid ""
"That's it! You now have ssh keys that can be used with Juju and other "
"applications that require ssh keys."
msgstr ""
